More than 220 fines and 380 warnings have been issued since restrictions came into effect on 1 February. CAPE TOWN - The City of Cape Town s water inspectorate is on Saturday cracking down on high water users in the Somerset West area.It s part of an intensified programme to reduce water usage and waste.Beefed up restrictions were imposed this month.The city's Xanthea Limberg says, Regular enforcement operations are happening on a daily basis across the city, in all suburbs and within the resources that the city have available. More than 220 fines and 380 warnings have been issued since restrictions came into effect.Last month, the Cape Town council adopted Level 3B water restrictions which took effect on 1 February.This after dam levels dropped to around 27% on average.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)